President Uhuru Kenyatta has made new appointments in government agencies, including the reappointment of former Attorney General Githu Muigai andÂ Nick Salat to plum state jobs. Muigai makes a reappearance as the non-executive chairperson of the Council of Legal Education, while KANU Secretary General Nick Salat has been appointed chairperson of the Agricultural Development Board for a three-year term. The Head of State also reappointed Kathleen Openda as chairperson of Kenya Institute of Mass Communication council and Andrew Musangi to the Public Procurement Regulatory Board. Other appointees include: Dr Andrew Kiplagat, chairperson, Kerio Valley Development
Authority board. Joe Ager, chairperson, National Mining Corporation board. John G. Msafari, chairperson, Kenya Fishing Industries Corporation board. Prof Elishiba Njambi Kimani, chairperson, Kenya Institute of Curriculum Development. Eva Adega Oduor, non-executive chairperson, Kenya Accreditation Service board. Dorothy Kimeu, chairperson, Special Economic Zones board. Nick Nesbitt, chairperson, Capital Markets Authority board. Ben Oluoch Olunya, chairperson, Export Processing Zones Authority. James Mureu, chairperson, Micro and Small Enterprises Authority. Phillip Charo, chairperson, Coast Development Authority. Edwin Kinyua, chairperson, board of directors of the East African Portland Cement Company Limited. Prof Ben Sihanya, chairperson, board of directors of the Kenya Institute for Public Policy Research and Analysis. Peter Musei Ntoyian, chairperson, board of directors of the Consolidated Bank Limited. Patrick Obath, chairperson, Board of Directors of the National Oil Corporation of Kenya. Kioko Kilukumi, chairperson, Energy and Petroleum Tribunal. Dr Dinah Mwinzi, chairperson, Kenya Industrial Research and Development Institute board. Video Of The Day: Former sports CS Hassan Wario convicted over Rio games scam